    "id": "skips-malformed-items",
    "severity": "MEDIUM",
    "category": "correctness",
    "location": "scripts/build/linear_pipeline.py:4564",
    "description": "The new activity_schema gate silently continues when an error-correction activity has a missing or non-list `items` field, and also skips non-mapping entries inside the list. That means malformed writer output such as `items: {incorrect: ...}` or a top-level alias shape can pass this gate with `checked: 0`, then fail later in `ActivityParser._parse_error_correction` with an unhelpful runtime error or publish an empty activity. Since this gate is intended to enforce the authoring schema early, strict-schema activity types should report these shapes as violations instead of skipping them."
  }
